  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Humanitarian Framework Agreement 2013, Red Cross</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Humanitarian Partnership Agreement 2013 is a strategic cooperation between MoFA and DRC regarding humanitarian interventions, in particular in protracted crises. The grant has supported activities in Afghanistan, Pakistan, Somalia, South Sudan, Kenya, Palestine and Syria, as well as thematic interventions such as mine action. A large part of the grant is allocated to ICRC appeals in support of people affected by conflict or other situations of violence (41%); a part is allocated to IFRC appeals in support of Red Cross Movement coordination and National Society capacity building (7%); and a part is allocated to bilateral humanitarian activities within the area of disaster response and National Society capacity building (19%). The remaining 33% is earmarked for the pool of Flexible Funds that enable DRC to respond quickly to acute crisis, providing humanitarian experts or funding for appeals. The grant is distributed with 29% for Africa, 10% for Asia, 19% for the Middle East and Northern Africa, 9% for interregional activities and 33% for the pool of Flexible Funds.</narrative>
  </description>
